Hon Gbenga Ayegbayo, the Chairman of Ejigbo Local Government Area of Osun State, has reportedly died. The deceased was battling with an undisclosed illness for months before finally succumbing to death on Monday. Ayegbayo died at a private hospital in Ogbomoso, Oyo State. It was gathered that Ayegbayo was a member of the ruling All Progressives Congress and was elected Chairman of Ejigbo LG in 2018. Recall that Ejigbo in Osun had been in the news recently after over 127 Ivory Coast returnees suspected to have contracted Coronavirus were camped at an isolation centre in the community. At least 17 of the returnees later tested positive for the virus and remain at the isolation facility in Ejigbo. Source OSOGBO - Following the panic induced by the story trending in the social media that six suspected coronavirus patients have escaped from the Ejigbo Isolation Centre, the Osun State Government has said that only one person is missing from the centre.The State Commissioner for Information and Civic Orientation, Mrs Funke… April 4, 2020 In "News" By Olajide Idowu Osogbo - The Osun government on Wednesday appealed to the Federal Government to come to its aid in containing the spread of COVID-19 in the state as confirmed cases rose to 14 from the initial two. Mr Ismail Omipidan, the Chief Press Secretary to Gov. Gboyega Oyetola,… April 1, 2020 In "News" By Victor Adeoti   Ejigbo    -     Prof. Isaac Adewole, the Minister of Health, on Monday commended the Gubernatorial Candidate of All Progressives Congress (APC) in Osun, Alhaji Isiaka Oyetola, for providing free medical care to 10,000 residents. Adewole made the commendation during the commencement of the free medical care in… September 10, 2018 In "News"